ce:section.ce:para:
The integrity of bacterial cell membranes was assessed according to the methods described in the references [

                           44

                        ]. For each kind of bacterial, the experiment was divided into six groups including control-black, control-light, GQDs-black group, GQDs-light group, GQDs@hMSN-black group and GQDs@hMSN-light group. The bacteria were incubated with each group of samples at 37 °C for 2 h. The absorbance of the samples at 260 nm was measured after filtration by 0.22 μm microporous membrane. The leakage of DNA, RNA, or proteins in the bacteria after sample treatment was calculated.
